140367.name: Courtyard Gate Key
140367.desc: Looks like a key to unlock a moon gate.

140370.name: Courtyard Gate Key
140370.desc: Looks like a key to unlock a moon gate.

140372.name: Family Photo
140372.desc: A picture of a family of three. On it is written: "When we first arrived in Xianzhou — Renault." It seems to be dated about a hundred years ago...

140373.name: Discarded Letter Sheets
140373.desc: A stack of discarded, unused letter paper. The owner seems to have written a few pages before stopping, much like a sudden and transient enthusiasm for learning.

140374.name: Rubbings on Paper
140374.desc: Text obtained through rubbing the faint engravings on a stone monument to a piece of tracing paper. Appears to have been intentionally left behind by the homeowner.

140376.name: Square Rice Ball
140376.desc: A square-shaped rice "ball" taken out of a lunchbox. Different foods are mixed together within. It might taste good?

140377.name: Shattered Cloud Knight Devastator Glaive
140377.desc: Broken weapon fragments, sharp enough to be used as a paper cutter.

140378.name: Old Bell
140378.desc: An old bell. It can produce a clear, crisp sound, and looks like an item used to attract small animals.

140380.name: Longevity Pill of Cruelty
140380.desc: A medicine exclusive to the Xianzhou Yaoqing, said to have the effect of improving overall fitness and rendering those who take it immune to all diseases for a short period of time. On the Yaoqing, legend holds that a healer who went by the surname of Yu fell in love with a foxian trader girl. But the Vidyadhara could live for a thousand years, much longer than the foxians. Yu searched for ways to release his lover from the grip of death. He fell for the trickery of the Disciples of Sanctus Medicus and asked his lover to take the longevity medicine of Abundance without telling her what it was. The foxian girl turned into an abomination that no longer loved him before being slain by the Cloud Knights. To prevent Yu, who was overwhelmed by grief, from becoming mara-struck, the Alchemy Commission ordered him to take the Longevity Pill of Cruelty that deprived him of love and desire until his demise. The legend has another version, in which Yu was not of the Vidyadhara but a mere mortal, and the foxian girl was a spy planted by the Disciples to infiltrate the Alchemy Commission. This version is not as popular, for it turns a romance story into a political power struggle. "Those who love and live deeply fall into mara, while those who sever desire and passions can live for a millennium. Ask yourself, then, why fear mara, and why take joy in a long life?"

140381.name: Unremarkable Trash
140381.desc: A trash bag filled with celestial jade tiles. Celestial jade tiles possess differing levels of rarity, and the sorting can be seen from the colors of the trash bags. "Enjoy responsibly, spend wisely."

140382.name: One-of-a-Kind Trash
140382.desc: A trash bag filled with celestial jade tiles. Celestial jade tiles possess differing levels of rarity, and the sorting can be seen from the colors of the trash bags. "Enjoy responsibly, spend wisely."

140383.name: Dispersed Heliobi
140383.desc: These appear to be heliobi fragments scattered across the land when Cirrus shattered. "Powerful heliobi can possibly swallow weaker ones and temporarily force them to be joined as one..." "However, upon being affected by an outside force, this equilibrium is also easy to collapse."

140384.name: Dispersed Heliobi
140384.desc: These appear to be heliobi fragments scattered across the land when Cirrus shattered. "Powerful heliobi can possibly swallow weaker ones and temporarily force them to be joined as one..." "However, upon being affected by an outside force, this equilibrium is also easy to collapse."

140385.name: Dispersed Heliobi
140385.desc: These appear to be heliobi fragments scattered across the land when Cirrus shattered. "Powerful heliobi can possibly swallow weaker ones and temporarily force them to be joined as one..." "However, upon being affected by an outside force, this equilibrium is also easy to collapse."

140386.name: Ordinary Trash
140386.desc: A trash bag filled with celestial jade tiles. Celestial jade tiles possess differing levels of rarity, and the sorting can be seen from the colors of the trash bags. "Enjoy responsibly, spend wisely."

140387.name: Unspectacular Trash
140387.desc: A trash bag filled with celestial jade tiles. Celestial jade tiles possess differing levels of rarity, and the sorting can be seen from the colors of the trash bags. "Enjoy responsibly, spend wisely."

140388.name: Average Trash
140388.desc: A trash bag filled with celestial jade tiles. Celestial jade tiles possess differing levels of rarity, and the sorting can be seen from the colors of the trash bags. "Enjoy responsibly, spend wisely."

140389.name: Common Trash
140389.desc: A trash bag filled with celestial jade tiles. Celestial jade tiles possess differing levels of rarity, and the sorting can be seen from the colors of the trash bags. "Enjoy responsibly, spend wisely."

140390.name: Unpretentious Trash
140390.desc: A trash bag filled with celestial jade tiles. Celestial jade tiles possess differing levels of rarity, and the sorting can be seen from the colors of the trash bags. "Enjoy responsibly, spend wisely."

140391.name: Lackluster Trash
140391.desc: A trash bag filled with celestial jade tiles. Celestial jade tiles possess differing levels of rarity, and the sorting can be seen from the colors of the trash bags. "Enjoy responsibly, spend wisely."

140392.name: Unnoteworthy Trash
140392.desc: A trash bag filled with celestial jade tiles. Celestial jade tiles possess differing levels of rarity, and the sorting can be seen from the colors of the trash bags. "Enjoy responsibly, spend wisely."

140393.name: Swarthy Trash
140393.desc: A trash bag filled with celestial jade tiles. Celestial jade tiles possess differing levels of rarity, and the sorting can be seen from the colors of the trash bags. "Enjoy responsibly, spend wisely."

140394.name: Numbers-got-Nerfed Trash
140394.desc: A trash bag filled with celestial jade tiles. Celestial jade tiles possess differing levels of rarity, and the sorting can be seen from the colors of the trash bags. "Enjoy responsibly, spend wisely."

140395.name: Emotion Prototype: The Moment of Betrayal
140395.desc: You will always remember the trust and gentleness of that person, the persuasion and incitement from those people, and the surprised whisper from that person the moment you drew your dagger. "Et tu, my child?"

140396.name: Emotion Prototype: The Cloud of Doubt
140396.desc:
You sit up, a cloud of sadness forming in your mind. The words you have promised to others begin to falter. Are you really not a loser? Can you really achieve anything? Have you really chosen the right path?
A fire ignites from the depths of your heart, and for one moment, tempting you to burn everything from the past to the ground.

140397.name: Emotion Prototype: Everlasting Hatred
140397.desc: As you read this message, please consider the following advice: Send a message to your nemesis and tell them that you have forgiven them. "Our lives are too short to be wasted on feuds."

140398.name: Emotion Prototype: Broken Dreams
140398.desc: Shards like this can be found everywhere throughout Penacony. They once belonged to broken hearts. "In the realm of black dreams I sleep, where distinctions of right or wrong are buried deep."

140399.name: Emotion Prototype: Momentary Freedom
140399.desc:
As the starship traverses the sky, leaving behind a trail of clouds, the IPC's pursuers disappear from sight. You exchange a high-five with your companions, feeling liberated from any constraints...
This is not the end. The looming threat of prison remains. It may be ten years or a hundred, but eventually, you will return to it. Until then, you can still savor a moment of freedom.

140400.name: Unknown Jigsaw Fragment
140400.desc:
This fragment appears to have been a part of a certain Dream Jigsaw.
You can feel from it a mixture of confusion, fear, grief, and an almost imperceptible determination to face death head-on.

140401.name: Firefly's Budget
140401.desc:
The meagre private funds of Firefly, a new artist of the Iris Family.
Use it wisely. It's someone else's money, after all.

140402.name: Cosmic Fried Rice (Overnight Edition)
140402.desc: The researchers' favorite work meal. It's not very fresh and not very clean. One wonders whether one will see the Aeons after eating it.

140403.name: Abnormal images from surveillance records
140403.desc: Surveillance images provided by the security robot. It records the suspicious figure that recently approached the door security system.

140404.name: External communication records
140404.desc: Data copied from the space station's terminal. It clearly and comprehensively records all external communication from the terminal.

140405.name: Freshly-Baked Cake
140405.desc: Fresh and tasty cake. Probably dropped by some unfortunate researcher.

140406.name: "Calm" Gear
140406.desc: A manifestation of the emotion "Calm" in the Dreamscape. It can be used to repair people's Emo Dial and recover their lost emotions or memories.

140407.name: "Happy" Gear
140407.desc: A manifestation of the emotion "Happy" in the Dreamscape. It can be used to repair people's Emo Dial and recover their lost emotions or memories.

140408.name: "Sad" Gear
140408.desc: A manifestation of the emotion "Sad" in the Dreamscape. It can be used to repair people's Emo Dial and recover their lost emotions or memories.

140409.name: "Angry" Gear
140409.desc: A manifestation of the emotion "Angry" in the Dreamscape. It can be used to repair people's Emo Dial and recover their lost emotions or memories.

140410.name: Lesley Dean's Rebirth Project
140410.desc: A petition calling on Lesley Dean's fans to enter the Dreamscape en masse and help him to "be reborn" through the Synesthesia Dreamscape.

140412.name: Half-Autographed Photo
140412.desc: Evidence that Lesley Dean once gained a new lease of life. "Not even death could extinguish his radiance."

140414.name: Aventurine's Token
140414.desc: A token of the Interastral Peace Corporation. You remember the envoy played a little trick with it.

140415.name: Steinway Falcon Luxury Speedster (Black)
140415.desc: A luxurious private Steinway Falcon Speedster, featuring a low-profile black color. "Steinway Falcon Speedster: Making your dream come true faster!"

140416.name: Steinway Falcon Luxury Speedster (Rental)
140416.desc: A luxurious private Steinway Falcon Speedster. The most commonly rented model. "Steinway Falcon Speedster: Making your dream come true faster!"

140417.name: Steinway Falcon Luxury Speedster (Gold)
140417.desc: A luxurious private Steinway Falcon Speedster, featuring an extravagant golden color. "Steinway Falcon Speedster: Making your dream come true faster!"

140418.name: Steinway Falcon Luxury Speedster (Blue)
140418.desc: A luxurious private Steinway Falcon Speedster, featuring a stylish blue color. "Steinway Falcon Speedster: Making your dream come true faster!"

140419.name: Utopon Unicycler
140419.desc: The luxury "Utopon" unicycler, inspired by wind instruments, boasts an elegant design and provides a safe riding experience without having to worry about traffic jams! "Transform every one of your trips into an unforgettable journey."

140420.name: Envision a Rose Forthcoming
140420.desc: An old record tape discovered at the hotel in the Dreamscape, containing a single track titled "Envision a Rose Forthcoming."

140421.name: Employees' Idle Chatter
140421.desc: Bocchi's co-workers seem to have a grudge against him because they are forced to work overtime. Feinman seems to have something to do with this.

140422.name: TV News
140422.desc: A news article about a swindler being caught. I'm writing this down, although I don't know how Bocchi can be related to the case.

140423.name: Project: Scarab
140423.desc: Bocchi's "Precious Proposal." You're uncertain whether it'll see any use.

140424.name: Bizarre Tape
140424.desc: A weird voicetape. A terrifying nightmare.

140425.name: Note: Searching for Mother in Dreamscape (I)
140425.desc: In the lobby of The Reverie, you encounter a father and daughter who seem to be searching for a long-lost relative in Penacony. Perhaps you will meet them again in Penacony's Dreamscape metropolis.

140426.name: Note: Searching for Mother in Dreamscape (II)
140426.desc: The father and daughter, seeking their relative's whereabouts in Penacony, inquire about a woman named "Charlotte the Dream Artist." A helpful banker informs them that artists in Penacony often gather in a restricted area known as the "Edge." Perhaps that will be their next destination.

140427.name: Note: Searching for Mother in Dreamscape (III)
140427.desc: Once more, you cross paths with the father and daughter at the Dream's Edge. They have yet to find Charlotte, however, they have discovered that Penacony's finest artists frequently assemble at The Reverie in the Dreamscape. Although the hotel in the Dreamscape is presently undergoing renovations, their determination remains unwavering as they plan to proceed there...

140428.name: Note: Searching for Mother in Dreamscape (IV)
140428.desc: In the end, the father and daughter locate their long-lost wife and mother at the hotel in the Dreamscape. However, she refuses to reunite with her family. Following a heartrending conversation, the father and daughter leave the dream world in frustration, leaving you wondering if you will ever encounter them in reality...

140429.name: Lucky One's Black Card
140429.desc:
The grand prize awarded by Dreamy Slots, but there are no instructions on how to use it.






...Well, for those who have read this far, it's unsightly to give you no hints. Let me tell you a secret: It's a room key.

140430.name: Golden Limited - Aideen Token
140430.desc:
This shiny gold token appears to hold great value and can potentially be exchanged for an incredible super jackpot, but nobody in the Golden Hour knows how to use it.
Nevertheless, remember the words: "Promising Future."

140431.name: Medicine of Unknown Use
140431.desc: A mysterious medicine Screwllum handed to you. It may evoke the memories buried deep within Professor Chadwick's consciousness.

140432.name: Eerie Building Block
140432.desc:
This box contains eerie puzzle building blocks. It can be returned to the Dream Ticker Administrator.
Puzzle blocks that make the Dream Tickers malfunction are sealed here, emitting an ominous aura.

140433.name: Ace Gambler's Discarded Part
140433.desc: A part given to you by an Intellitron guest known as the "Ace Gambler." Its purpose remains a mystery. "Just carry it with you, even if as a talisman."

140434.name: Ace Gambler's Precious Part
140434.desc: A part given to you by an Intellitron guest known as the "Ace Gambler." It is said to contain a miniature transmitter that manipulates the outcome of the capsule machine, but it is no longer functional. "Don't frown all day. Put a smile on that face!"

140435.name: Soulheal Special Mix
140435.desc: A special beverage given to you by Giovanna the dream nurse. It helps to suppress negative emotions and assists people in engaging with their normal jobs and lives.

140436.name: Components From a Certain Ruin
140436.desc: This is a part found in the ruins of the Pasdrak City Civic Center. Its original purpose is now impossible to discover. Swanga now carries this part with him at all times as a reminder to always recall the blood and tears of the revolutionaries.

140437.name: Handwritten Letter
140437.desc: A delicately wrapped letter by Pom-Pom with a message expressing gratitude. "Thank you for the gift, passenger {NICKNAME}!"

140438.name: Handwritten Letter
140438.desc: A delicately wrapped letter by Dan Heng with a message expressing gratitude. "Thank you for your gift. I like it."

140439.name: Handwritten Letter
140439.desc: A delicately wrapped letter by Welt with a message expressing gratitude. "Thanks for the candy. I'll keep the rest for when we all come back to share."

140440.name: Fate's Epistle
140440.desc: The parting gift from Black Swan. A tiny card numbered 'Zero,' seemingly absent from Black Swan's collection. In the card's art, she casts her gaze into the mist of destiny. "If one day you have unfortunately sunk into the Memory Zone's deep seas without a Memokeeper by yourself — it will guide you out on my behalf."

140441.name: Invite Received by the Annihilation Gang

140442.name: Gulliver's Arch
140442.desc: The entrance to the Dewlight Pavilion's Dreamscape Sandpit. Placing your hand through the small archway shrinks your body, and stepping out through the door in miniature state restores your original form. "The appearance of this thing reminds me of a tunnel that could shrink people with a single pass..." "If I were you, I would immediately shut your mouth. Don't say things that are not meant to be said."

140443.name: Pinball Machine Model
140443.desc: Pinball Machine Model. A miniature version of the Soulglad Candyball launcher found throughout the Sweetdream Paradise. "What would happen if I put a candyball into Soulglad?" "You can give it a try, but when the Bloodhound Family interrogates you, remember not to involve me in it."

140444.name: Aventurine's Cornerstone
140444.desc: The cornerstone that only belongs to you. The Ten Stonehearts must cut their Cornerstone with their own will, allowing it to radiate its unique brilliance. Though shattered, the divine corpus of Qlipoth still shines for you. "All or nothing, it shall be."

140447.name: Aventurine's Baggage
140447.desc: A baggage that only belongs to you. Filled with precious gems, it also serves as a tool for your tricky and elaborate magic trick. "Believing that you can trade these base and tacky jewels for everything — That's what gamblers excel at, isn't it?"

140449.name: Mundanite's Insight
140449.desc: A most exquisite scroll, holding a doctor's prescription within. Dr. Ratio advises you to only unveil it in a moment of life or death. "You look distressed. Is something troubling you? If so, you can figure it out yourself."

140450.name: "Mutually Assured Destruction" Button
140450.desc: A cute-looking button with an adorable design. Seemingly capable of triggering the complete annihilation of the other button holder, along with the entire Penacony — Can this be true? "For she is fair."

140451.name: Special Drink "El Dorado"
140451.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'El Dorado' in your honor, Dreamchaser —" "To golden dreams."

140452.name: Special Drink "The Premature Burial"
140452.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'The Premature Burial' in your honor, dreamer —" "To bringing time to a standstill."

140453.name: Special Drink "Dream Within Dream"
140453.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'Dream Within Dream' in your honor, sober one —" "To our forebearers who dug their own graves."

140454.name: Special Drink "The Big Sleep"
140454.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'The Big Sleep' in your honor, lost sheep —" "Here's to the ghosts of the past."

140455.name: Special Drink "The Long Goodbye"
140455.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'The Long Goodbye' in your honor, watcher —" "To a bitter childhood."

140456.name: Special Drink "Farewell, My Lovely"
140456.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'Farewell, My Lovely' in your honor, seeker of truth —" "To unfinished business."

140457.name: Special Drink "A Ticket to the Boneyard"
140457.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'A Ticket to the Boneyard' in your honor, Nameless —" "To the dead and the dying."

140458.name: Special Drink "Even the Wicked"
140458.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'Even the Wicked' in your honor, Trailblazer —" "To the sad truth."

140459.name: Special Drink "Time to Murder and Create"
140459.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'Time to Murder and Create' in your honor, innovator —" "To great vengeance."

140465.name: Commemorative Photo
140465.desc: A photograph exclusively yours. "May your schemes be forever concealed."

140466.name: Hanu's Dream Bubble
140466.desc: The reward for beating the game Hanu's Prison Break, capturing all of Hanu's highlights in the story. Perhaps similar scenes did happen in real history.

140468.name: Indefinite Patent Operative Omnifier
140468.desc: This item is used to defend the legal rights of the great inventor Emmr... Ahem, well, to defend the legal rights of all creators in the cosmos.

140469.name: "Happy" Gear
140469.desc: Extract emotions of "happiness" from passersby to fill in the missing aspects for the Dreamweaver's Emo Dial.

140470.name: Oksana's "Toys"
140470.desc: Taking a peek into the immaculate bag, you see it's filled with ordinary toys. You cannot understand how they're selling so well. Perhaps this is what Oksana might call a return of "goodwill."

140471.name: Mr. Bigwig's Jigsaw Fragment
140471.desc:
This fragment appears to have been a part of a certain Dream Jigsaw.
You can feel from it a mixture of yearning and anticipation for the future.

140472.name: Spade's Jigsaw Fragment
140472.desc:
This fragment appears to have been a part of a certain Dream Jigsaw.
You can feel from it a mixture of yearning and anticipation for the future.

140473.name: Melancholy's Jigsaw Fragment
140473.desc:
This fragment appears to have been a part of a certain Dream Jigsaw.
You can feel from it a mixture of yearning and anticipation for the future.

140474.name: Starlet's Jigsaw Fragment
140474.desc:
This fragment appears to have been a part of a certain Dream Jigsaw.
You can feel from it a mixture of yearning and anticipation for the future.

140475.name: Lady's Jigsaw Fragment
140475.desc:
This fragment appears to have been a part of a certain Dream Jigsaw.
You can feel from it a mixture of yearning and anticipation for the future.

140476.name: Tin Man's Jigsaw Fragment
140476.desc:
This fragment appears to have been a part of a certain Dream Jigsaw.
You can feel from it a mixture of yearning and anticipation for the future.

140477.name: "The Dreamweaver Archives"
140477.desc: Sir Whittaker always kept the files containing information about the legendary Dreamweavers of the past.

140478.name: Photo From the Archives
140478.desc: An old photograph. It looks dated, with four young figures printed on its faded yellow photo paper.

140479.name: Dreamweavers' Group Photo
140479.desc: A familiar photo bearing the images of four legendary Dreamweavers. You once used it to unlock Dr. Blues' heart.

140483.name: Mr. Soda's Extras Film Reel
140483.desc: Contains the extra content of the animated film series Clockie: Dreamjoy Memoir, telling the story of Dreamville's merchant, "Mr. Soda." *gurgle* Grab a bottle of SoulGlad, make your dreams a blast!

140484.name: Brother Hanu's Extras Film Reel
140484.desc: Contains the extra content of the animated film series Clockie: Dreamjoy Memoir, telling the story of Dreamville's Big Brother Hanu. An extremely cool *hmph*.

140485.name: Boss Stone's Extras Film Reel
140485.desc: Contains the extra content of the animated film series Clockie: Dreamjoy Memoir, telling the story of Dreamville's enemy, Boss Stone. Wahaha, Dreamville is mine!

140486.name: Origami Bird's Extras Film Reel
140486.desc: Contains the extra content of the animated film series Clockie: Dreamjoy Memoir, telling the story of Dreamville's builder, Origami Bird. Tweet, make this small town bigger and more beautiful, tweet!

140487.name: Old Man Wood's Extras Film Reel
140487.desc: Contains the extra content of the animated film series Clockie: Dreamjoy Memoir, telling the story of Dreamville's savior, Old Man Wood. *cough cough* Everyone should love and respect each other, and more importantly, respect the rules.

140488.name: Hamster Ball Knight's Extras Film Reel
140488.desc: Contains the extra content of the animated film series Clockie: Dreamjoy Memoir, telling the story of Dreamville's Spheroid star, Hamster Ball Knight. Let's have a contest! Go go go go!

140489.name: Bitter Dreams
140489.desc: Death is a bitter truth, but what you did will be remembered by history.

140490.name: Drowning Sweetness
140490.desc: The spirit of freedom will spread far and wide among the stars, and its legacy will be more timeless than a pastoral song.

140491.name: Sparkle's Wondrous Treasure Map
140491.desc:
Miss Sparkle thoughtfully marked the locations of (five of the 999) imaginary neutron bombs for you — she's just too kind!
Where are the rest of them, you ask? Just take a few strolls around on this luxury airship~

140492.name: Lost Property
140492.desc: A notebook lost by someone — its corners are yellowed and the majority of the notes within have been rendered incomprehensible by some kind of red rust-like stains.

140493.name: Big Ticker's Broken Heart (I)
140493.desc: A single part of a lost heart that has fallen into an existential crisis. "They said that the Dreamscape Ticker isn't the same as Clockie at all, just a scrapped early Clockie prototype..."

140494.name: Big Ticker's Broken Heart (II)
140494.desc: A single part of a lost heart that has fallen into an existential crisis. "Please... just leave me be, Clockie. I just don't know how to face you... because I'm just a failed product."

140495.name: Big Ticker's Broken Heart (III)
140495.desc: A single part of a lost heart that has fallen into an existential crisis. "I... I'll never be qualified to be the real you. Just give up, Clockie!"

140498.name: Television (Limited Edition)
140498.desc: Made locally in Penacony, this television appears ordinary but is actually a commemorative TV set for Lil' Brother Hanu, allowing users to transform into Brother Hanu at any time and relive that wonderful adventure story. "Wishing you have fun, and may you never forget the deeds of Hanunue."

140499.name: Symbol of Fortune
140499.desc: A seemingly ordinary Aideen Token that contains the luck that Aventurine wishes to pass to you. "Using this coin, I won the capsule machine's grand prize seven times in a row. Hopefully, it can bring you good luck as well. — Aventurine"

140500.name: Astral Express Miniature (Limited Edition)
140500.desc: A miniature model based on the current Astral Express. A very expensive limited edition item paid for by Aventurine himself. "Here's a small token of congratulations to the Astral Express for obtaining the Radiant Feldspar — Aventurine"

140501.name: Page of Past Dreams
140501.desc:
A boy's graffiti. The strokes are immature, yet time has not worn down the imagery of old dreams even a bit.
His faithful companion has put in a lot of effort for this.

140502.name: Hex Pass
140502.desc: A premium gaming subscription service newly released by the Hex Club. Designed by Think-Tank, players can challenge "Hexanexus: Remake" and obtain rewards from various tiers. "Listen up. This is what sunk cost looks like."

140503.name: An Elder's Note
140503.desc: A mysterious note that seems to contain an encryption key and some ciphers. "The Ten-Lords Commission knows what these documents mean, of course. They just don't know where the contents will be used."

140507.name: Denisovan Slumbernana Pendant
140507.desc: A pendant decorated with a Slumbernana Monkey trinket, serving as a promotional reward for "Denisovan" level members. Proud members flaunt it on their phones, fanny packs, necks, or even faces. "Oh, by the way, 'Human' level members can accumulate pendant shards from the daily quiz and class attendance."

140508.name: Slumbernana Association Membership Card (Golden Slumbernana)
140508.desc: This card has a golden slumbernana printed on it, signifying official membership of the Slumbernana Association. Whoever holds this card will be seen as a friend of all Slumbernana Monkey fans. "Rumor has it that only 0.6% of membership cards have a jadegreen banana printed on it, but members who have recruited over 90 fresh monkeys for the Association will always get that rare card."

140509.name: Memory-Peeking Film
140509.desc: An enigmatic film reel given to you by Mr. Reca. The eye attached to it casts an unsettling and penetrating gaze, emanating a powerful obsession toward witnessing something. Entering another's Emoscape using this item allows you to capture the memories you have witnessed as audiovisual records. "Memories are movies without a montage, while movies are memories that have been edited. The former is raw material, and the latter is art refined from it. Regrettably, most of my colleagues fixate on the former, and are unable to create the latter..."

140510.name: Luofu Sports Illustrated — Special Edition for Luka's Final
140510.desc: The special edition of Luofu Sports Illustrated, reporting on Luka's participation in the "Ringmaster's Challenge." "Swinging the next hit is always what's most important!"

140511.name: SoulGlad Bottle Cap
140511.desc: A bottle cap, purchased from the Dreamjolt Troupe for a high price. The fact remains that bottle caps are valuable even outside of nuclear wastelands.

140512.name: Slumbernana Monkey Pre-Order Special Freebie
140512.desc: A special freebie for pre-ordering Slumbernana Monkey dolls, showcasing sub-par quality. Once the dolls arrive, the monkey dolls will autonomously follow the signal from this freebie to reach its purchaser. "Why do we give a lousy doll to the buyers first, BananAdvisor?" "1. To enhance the quality of the official doll. 2. To provide instant positive feedback upon their purchase. 3. To offer them a means to show off on social platforms before the goods arrive."

140513.name: Castrum Kremnos Crest
140513.desc: A crest representing the benediction of Nikador — Titankins bearing this crest often proclaim their glory and invincibility in battle. "What a high drop rate! Thank you for your generosity, Nikador!"

140514.name: Group Photo of March 7th and the Crew
140514.desc: After using it in your Inventory, you can view the group photo.

140515.name: Group Photo of March 7th and Friends
140515.desc: After using it in your Inventory, you can view the group photo.

140516.name: Group Photo of March 7th and the Crew
140516.desc: After using it in your Inventory, you can view the group photo.

140517.name: Group Photo of March 7th and Friends
140517.desc: After using it in your Inventory, you can view the group photo.

140518.name: "Camereidoscope"
140518.desc: A camera lens gifted by Sparkle. To this day, you still are unsure of its exact use. "Transient and never repeating. Is capturing the vibrant scenes within the kaleidoscope merely a futile wishful thinking?"

140519.name: Bard's Memory Fragment
140519.desc: This memory of Castrum Kremnos comes from a bard, who praises the never-ending glory of the Strife Titan.

140520.name: Chartonus' Memory Fragment
140520.desc: This memory of Castrum Kremnos originates from the Grand Craftsman Chartonus, seemingly carrying with it the profound and weighty history of the Mountain Dwellers.

140521.name: Damionis' Memory Fragment
140521.desc: This memory of Castrum Kremnos stems from an adventurer named Damionis, showcasing the golden era of the city's grandeur.

140522.name: Tingyun's Dream Bubble
140522.desc: A dream bubble gifted by Tingyun, which records your journeys on the Xianzhou. In this dream, the real Tingyun never missed out on meeting you. "The future is neither an initial meeting nor a reunion — We have always walked together."

140523.name: Cheap Supplies
140523.desc: The cheapest food available — some of it already spoiled — but for the starving, there's no room for choice.

140524.name: Standard Supplies
140524.desc: Fresh food with simple, balanced nutrition. Commoners might tolerate it for a few meals, but for those on the brink of starvation, it tastes as sweet as honey.

140525.name: Luxurious Supplies
140525.desc: Exquisitely refined dishes, each a delicate masterpiece. An ordinary family may savor them for a week, while the starving would be swept straight to heaven with each bite.

140526.name: Golden Remains
140526.desc: A trophy obtained after completing a mysterious challenge. If you listen carefully, you will hear some mournful mutters reverberating within the hollow skull. "This is what paradise is like: Those who know that it is a paradise cannot return. Those who do not know it is a paradise seek wonderland within its expanse."

140527.name: Portentous Goldwoven: Abyss of Fate
140527.desc: A tome containing prophecies. Upon closer inspection, one will discover that the scroll is woven from golden threads. "There is a prophecy within that will only be revealed to the one who opens the scroll."

140528.name: Portentous Goldwoven: Abyss of Fate
140528.desc: A tome containing prophecies. Upon closer inspection, one will discover that the scroll is woven from golden threads. "There is a prophecy within that will only be revealed to the one who opens the scroll."

140529.name: Portentous Goldwoven: Abyss of Fate
140529.desc: A tome containing prophecies. Upon closer inspection, one will discover that the scroll is woven from golden threads. "There is a prophecy within that will only be revealed to the one who opens the scroll."

140530.name: Portentous Goldwoven: Abyss of Fate
140530.desc: A tome containing prophecies. Upon closer inspection, one will discover that the scroll is woven from golden threads. "There is a prophecy within that will only be revealed to the one who opens the scroll."

140531.name: Memory Crystal Shard
140531.desc: Strange crystals that store the power of Remembrance appear as you journey along. The light and shadows cast by the crystals seem to play out familiar scenes, and if you place them close to your ear, you can even hear the familiar whispers...

140532.name: Golden Bough of Vows
140532.desc:
Strange aquatic flowers, their sheen dazzling and warm.
It is said that they are tokens of the eternal vows between two revered deities.

140533.name: Burning Golden Bough of Vows
140533.desc:
Strange aquatic flowers, their amber-colored soft flames sway imperceptibly.
It is said that they are tokens of the eternal vows between two revered deities, and now it holds the soul of one of them.

140534.name: Steel Claw Dagger with Faded Patterns
140534.desc: A Steelclaw Dagger, a type of weapon unique to Castrum Kremnos. Its grip shows signs of wear, with the patterns faded, giving it the look of an old blade.

140535.name: Dull Kremnos Shield
140535.desc: The Kremnos Shield, a type of weapon unique to Castrum Kremnos. It just has a slightly dull coloration, giving it an aged appearance.

140536.name: Relatively Small Greatsword of Kremnos
140536.desc: A Kremnos Greatsword, a type of weapon unique to Castrum Kremnos. Its blade appears to be fractured, as though it has been reforged.

140537.name: Portentous Goldwoven: Strife Ruins
140537.desc: A tome containing prophecies. Upon closer inspection, one will discover that the scroll is woven from golden threads. "There is a prophecy within that will only be revealed to the one who opens the scroll."

140538.name: Portentous Goldwoven: Bloodbathed Battlefront
140538.desc: A tome containing prophecies. Upon closer inspection, one will discover that the scroll is woven from golden threads. "There is a prophecy within that will only be revealed to the one who opens the scroll."

140539.name: Georios' Embers
140539.desc: An ancient-looking torch, said to hold the last unextinguished cinders of Georios. When the long night descends, it might bring a glimmer of light to a world in darkness. "Heh, if you're afraid of the dark, just keep me by your side."

140540.name: March 7th's Camera
140540.desc: A camera entrusted to you by your dear companion, March 7th. Taking her alias into account... Perhaps this camera is actually March 7th's true form. "Remember to take more photographs. I'll check on you!"

140541.name: Scroll of Mysterious Rites
140541.desc: A tattered scroll detailing the steps of an ancient, mysterious ritual, with annotations from an unknown person. "Who knows what this might summon..."

140542.name: Artwork Nikador Battles the Rosy Celestial Maiden
140542.desc: A painting from the Rosy Celestial Maiden series, released by an opportunistic art dealer. You can't help but chuckle upon seeing March 7th's dashing form as she fights in this painting. "Street stall art can never go out of style."

140543.name: Old Kremnos Festival Photo
140543.desc: An old photograph of the Kremnos Festival, taken by Damionis. Though slightly blurred, it still faintly captures the grand scale of the festival.

140544.name: Small Amount of Redsoil Feed
140544.desc: Exceptionally pure redsoil feed, crafted with the ideal wet-to-dry ratio. It's the absolute favorite treat of dromases.

140545.name: Mystical Blacksoil
140545.desc: An essential sacrificial item for a mysterious ritual. It's somewhat clotted.

140546.name: Mystical Seeds
140546.desc: An essential sacrificial item for a mysterious ritual. It looks slightly dried up.

140547.name: Mystical Philter
140547.desc: An essential sacrificial item for a mysterious ritual. It smells a little sour.

140548.name: Scroll of Mysterious Rites
140548.desc: A tattered scroll detailing the steps of an ancient, mysterious ritual, with annotations from an unknown person. "Who knows what this might summon..."

140549.name: Scroll of Mysterious Rites
140549.desc: A tattered scroll detailing the steps of an ancient, mysterious ritual, with annotations from an unknown person. "Who knows what this might summon..."

140550.name: Mysterious Gift (L)
140550.desc: A mysterious gift hidden behind the door, looking very valuable. What could it be?

140551.name: Mysterious Gift (S)
140551.desc: A mysterious gift hidden behind the door, looking somewhat plain in appearance. What could it be?

140552.name: Slate
140552.desc: A slate that is hidden by Possephone within the cushion. Its contents appear to reveal why Hadez acted against her.

140553.name: Teleslate
140553.desc: A teleslate belonging to Possephone. From the memory you observed, it seems there was a glimmer of hope that Possephone could have escaped from Hadez.

140554.name: Scroll
140554.desc: A tattered and torn scroll. Based on the memory you observed, it is a replica of the one Rhadaman used to trap the married couple.

140556.name: Janus Priest's Talisman
140556.desc: A stone seal that symbolizes one's identity as a priest of Janus. It can resound with and open the Gate of Infinity.

140557.name: Seal Slammers Photo Slate
140557.desc: Use from your Inventory to view the group photo.

140558.name: Seal Slammers Photo Slate
140558.desc: Use from your Inventory to view the group photo.

140559.name: Nicomachus' Work Permit
140559.desc: A bloodied Grove of Epiphany work permit with the name "Nicomachus."

140560.name: Andreas' Work Permit
140560.desc: A damaged Grove of Epiphany work permit with the name "Andreas."

140561.name: Clio's Work Permit
140561.desc: A Grove of Epiphany work permit wrinkled with sweat with the name "Clio."

140562.name: Clio's Experimental Crop
140562.desc: A grain that is quite ordinary in realms beyond the sky but uncommon in Amphoreus. The label on the specimen indicates it is the 330th generation of an experiment — perhaps the experiment has been ongoing for centuries. "During the breeding process, the crop's resistance to the black tide has significantly improved. The next step will attempt to enable the crops to absorb energy from the black tide and survive in lightless environments, challenging the conventional belief that no life can endure within the black tide."

140563.name: Nicomachus' Notebook
140563.desc: A seemingly unremarkable scroll filled with various equations and symbols, so complex that even the Synesthesia Beacon struggles to provide a reliable translation. "Self-reference is the most challenging problem — it not only strips mathematics of its completeness but also renders our souls enigmatic within the logical system." "This equation should hold true. I have an excellent proof... but alas, the space here is too tiny for it."

140564.name: Andreas' Ceremonial Medicine Enhancer
140564.desc: It is said that this somewhat hazardous-looking powder helps participants in Titan-worship ceremonies attune their consciousness to the thoughts of the Titans. "So, what exactly is it made of?" "An unrefined plant-based sugar." "Huh? So eating it just means eating sugar?" "Yes. The ceremonies are quite lengthy, and fasting participants often struggle to endure due to low blood sugar." "..."

140565.name: Artakama's Sword
140565.desc: The sword once wielded by Artakama, a Chrysos Heir scholar of the Grove. In the dire battle against the black tide, this sword stood steadfast by its master until her final breath. Following Artakama's demise, her younger sister, Cynane, picked up the sword and continued the fight until the ceaseless swarms of monsters devoured everything living.

140566.name: Dew of Divine Blood
140566.desc:
A rare Amphorean fine wine. It is said to be brewed from crops nourished by the divine blood of each Titan.
This particular bottle originates from the Chrysalis of Gold, Mnestia of Romance.

140567.name: Weft
140567.desc: A golden spindle that belongs to "Goldweaver" Aglaea. A legendary treasure. "Follow the golden thread, the love that contains all like the gods."

140568.name: "Work Champion" Medal
140568.desc: A memorial medal issued by the Garden of Life to reward the sweat and tears shed by Chimera Squad that took the crown. "To the most diligent chimera. We hope to see growth and improvement in your future work!"

140569.name: Coreflame of Time
140569.desc: The fallen soul of Oronyx the Time Titan. The Coreflame urgently awaits to return to its place, and its demigod will assume the authority of the vacant station after completing the trial.

140570.name: Nether Butterfly's Pondering
140570.desc: A handcrafted silver ring — if you hold it to your ear, you can hear the sound of melting snow. In Aidonia, the departed seal ice and snow into a ring before their final journey, offering it to the living as a token to walk the rest of the path in their stead. "When the ice melts and the snow fades, the flowers will bloom, and you will find me."

140571.name: Letter from the Phantom Thief Cipher
140571.desc: A phantom thief's letter left behind by Kitty Phantom Thief, Cipher, out of "courtesy" and "honor." "I fear it would attract tasteless little thieves, so I shall safeguard it for now."

140572.name: Cipher's Coin
140572.desc: A coin left behind by Kitty Phantom Thief, Cipher, out of "courtesy" and "honor." "Naturally, I've left appropriate payment — a single coin."

140573.name: Trianne's Hand-Drawn Picture
140573.desc: Trianne secretly prepared a small gift for Castorice — a childlike drawing of the companions on their Flame-Chase Journey. Castorice perceptively noticed that it, and the memory it represents, would be the key to saving {NICKNAME} from the nether realm. "But Little Cas no longer has anything to fear now, because everyone is here with you in this Flame-Chase Journey!"

140574.name: Coreflame of Death
140574.desc: The fallen soul of Thanatos the Death Titan. The Coreflame urgently awaits to return to its place. The demigod of Death has already overcome the trial and assumed the authority of the Titan.

140575.name: Outlander King of Knights Puppet
140575.desc: The memory entity you carried away from a dream, in some foreign land, an artisan who admired the King and carved a puppet with heartfelt reverence. Though it seems far removed from the real King, and the craftsmanship leaves much to be desired, what heroes pass down to later generations is often just like this — crude, yet enough to soothe the soul. "Besides, don't you think that, after staring at it for a while, it actually kind of feels full of soul?" "I think it's trying to suck my soul in!"

140576.name: Tarnished Glory
140576.desc: An old, tattered photograph captures the past of Miss Note — the cries of injustice behind bars, the jubilant song upon breaking free, the thunderous applause beneath the stage, the scorn born of disgrace. All those voices have faded into history, leaving only a yellowed memory behind. "And even so, I still choose to sing."

140577.name: Chronocognitive Anchor
140577.desc:
A Curio and Space Anchor from the world of Erudition that protects your individual data structure from the influences of digital tsunamis.
When necessary, it can also serve as a bridge for communications between the internal and external world.

140578.name: "Take the Feast to Tomorrow"
140578.desc: It was a distant wish, and also her blessing.

140579.name: "Golden Dew"
140579.desc: Rich, intense, sweet. Not exactly sweet, but the contrast is obvious.

140580.name: "Scarlet Honey Brew"
140580.desc: The bottle contains the heroic souls of pomegranates who fought to their last breath. Drink it, and honor their journey.

140581.name: "Colorful Gate"
140581.desc: You can taste all the Amphorean fruits in this! Zero intoxication level, totally safe and worry-free!

140582.name: "Dark River of Souls"
140582.desc: Don't worry. It just looks like water from the River of Souls... probably.

140583.name: "To Dromas"
140583.desc: Thoughts flowed like a fountain. By the time the pen stopped, only half a bottle of honey brew remained.

140584.name: "Cloud Brew"
140584.desc: Harvesting grape clouds at the intersection of Evernight for extraction and bottling... mysterious purple-tinted... plain drinking water.

140585.name: "Rough-Brew Ambrosia!"
140585.desc: The kitty doesn't want to think about why this bottle of ambrosia has an exclamation mark in its name, and honestly, she has no clue either.

140586.name: "Scorching Like Fire in My Memories"
140586.desc: The taste hits you like a punch to the face. Might be just what you need for healing wounds.

140587.name: "The Deep Sea"
140587.desc: Tides rise and fall, but the sound of waves remains eternal.

140588.name: "Have Mercy, Okhema"
140588.desc: Despite the oddly saccharine naming sense, the complimentary drinks in the Marmoreal Palace guest rooms taste just ordinarily sweet.

140589.name: Flame-Chase Medallion
140589.desc: An identification badge of the Flame-Chase Army, bearing the Imperator's highest command. The wearer has unrestricted access throughout the city.

140590.name: Hysilens's Ceramic Cup
140590.desc: An unassuming ceramic cup, plain in craftsmanship. At that wanton feast, its cold rim passed her honey brew to your lips, branding you with the sin of exile, yet bestowing a dream of clarity in return. "The worth of a vessel lies in what it once held, and who once held it, just as blades earn legend by battle, and heroes are remembered through sacrifice."

140591.name: Dew of Divine Blood
140591.desc:
Phagousa was said to have buried twelve bottles of fine vintage beneath the seabed, hoping to savor them a thousand years later. But even as the black tide silenced the song of Chalice of Plenty, not a single drop had been uncorked.

This bottle, sweetest of the twelve vintages, was brought ashore by the last surviving sea siren. The divine power it holds can pierce through any fog.

140592.name: Coreflame of Worldbearing
140592.desc: The Worldbearing Titan, Kephale's fallen soul. Yet seemingly some foreign force has tampered with them, making their divinity different from the one in the past Cycle. The Coreflame awaits its rightful return, through which the final Deliverer shall forge a new Era Nova.

140593.name: Flame-Chase Medallion
140593.desc: An identification badge of the Flame-Chase Army, bearing the Imperator's highest command. The wearer has unrestricted access throughout the city.

140594.name: Hysilens's Ceramic Cup
140594.desc: An unassuming ceramic cup, plain in craftsmanship. At that wanton feast, its cold rim passed her honey brew to your lips, branding you with the sin of exile, yet bestowing a dream of clarity in return. "The worth of a vessel lies in what it once held, and who once held it, just as blades earn legend by battle, and heroes are remembered through sacrifice."

140595.name: Dew of Divine Blood
140595.desc:
Phagousa was said to have buried twelve bottles of fine vintage beneath the seabed, hoping to savor them a thousand years later. But even as the black tide silenced the song of Chalice of Plenty, not a single drop had been uncorked.

This bottle, sweetest of the twelve vintages, was brought ashore by the last surviving sea siren. The divine power it holds can pierce through any fog.

140596.name: Chronocognitive Anchor
140596.desc:
A Curio. A Space Anchor in a world of Erudition. It can protect individual data structures from the influences of digital tsunamis.
When necessary, it can also serve as a bridge for communications between the internal and external world.

140597.name: Dream's Curtain Call
140597.desc: A photo taken at an unknown time, but the reality of its touch is undeniable. In the past, this scene truly came to pass, leaving behind a proof of its transpiration. Though few are aware, a young girl will smile when she recalls a beautiful dream she once had. The dreamer is also the dream-maker. The dream-maker is also the dreamer. Only by offering up one's past can the most beautiful dreams be woven. People will not lose themselves within them, unwilling to awaken. In their beautiful dreams, they will regain the courage to face the future. And then, walk toward tomorrow.

140598.name: Dream's Curtain Call
140598.desc: You decide how memories are ultimately presented. When that beautiful dream ended, you immortalized Firefly in the way she longed for. The dreamer is also the dream-maker. The dream-maker is also the dreamer. Only by offering up one's past can the most beautiful dreams be woven. People will not lose themselves within them, unwilling to awaken. In their beautiful dreams, they will regain the courage to face the future. And then, walk toward tomorrow.

140599.name: Imperial Ring of Strife
140599.desc: From the "Champion of Strife": Mydei's bestowal, symbolizing both his glory and restraint as a ruler and protector.

140600.name: Trickery Coin
140600.desc: From the "Trickery's Traveler": Cipher's bestowal, symbolizing her playful yet sincere blessings and desires.

140601.name: Winter Blossom of Death
140601.desc: From the "Servant of the Afterlife": Castorice's bestowal, symbolizing the tenacity and peace she watches over on the other side.

140602.name: Passage Plushie
140602.desc: From the "Holy Child of Passage": Tribios's bestowal, symbolizing her unwavering faith and empathy throughout her journey in a thousand bodies.

140603.name: Bracelet of Romance
140603.desc: From the "Weaver of Romance": Aglaea's bestowal, symbolizing her unchanging selflessness and temperance beneath her aloof perfection.

140604.name: Skybound Spirit Kist
140604.desc: From the "Healer of the Sky": Hyacine's bestowal, symbolizing her gentle devotion and indiscriminate love for all of humanity.

140605.name: Jade of Reason
140605.desc: From the "Scholar of Reason": Anaxa's bestowal, symbolizing the enlightenment and critique he calmly left for future generations.

140606.name: Wish of Worldbearing
140606.desc: To save the world, one must shoulder the burden of heavy wishes. Only by leaving it behind, can you absolve the obsession.

140607.name: Despair of Worldbearing
140607.desc: To save the world, one must be accompanied by searing despair. Only by shattering it, can you absolve the obsession.

149957.name: Photo With March 7th
149957.desc: {NICKNAME} and March 7th's group photo. "We adventure together, explore together, and capture wonderful memories together. In the journeys to come, we will "trailblaze" more beautiful moments, preserving them with our camera, our eyes, and our hearts."

149958.name: Photo With March 7th
149958.desc: {NICKNAME} and March 7th's group photo. "We adventure together, explore together, and capture wonderful memories together. In the journeys to come, we will "trailblaze" more beautiful moments, preserving them with our camera, our eyes, and our hearts."

149959.name: Thermic Core
149959.desc: Modified by Serval, the Silvermane Guards' Snowshine Lamps can now automatically transfer kindlings.

149975.name: Blurry Photo
149975.desc: An old yellowing photo. Evidence of a certain individual's part in a certain historic event. The figure in the picture did not seem to plan to let people feel the historical weight this photo should carry. "What will become of Belobog in a hundred years? Well, you'll have to see it through your eyes."

149976.name: Blurry Portrait
149976.desc: A small circular frame with a portrait within. Evidence of a certain individual's part in a certain historic event. The figure in the picture did not seem to plan to let people feel the historical weight this photo should carry. "What will become of Belobog in a hundred years? Well, you'll have to see it through your eyes."

149977.name: Portrait With a Clue
149977.desc: A small circular frame with a portrait. The expression of the man dressed in an old military uniform in the frame is... complicated. A clockwise-pointing arrow is drawn on the back, accompanied by the phrase "The next clue sleeps soundly in the shade of the arch." "What will become of Belobog in a hundred years? Well, you'll have to see it through your eyes."

149978.name: Pela's Notes
149978.desc: Pela's notes with her elegant handwriting. In the note, there is a curved arrow pointing clockwise and another pointing counterclockwise. Next to the drawing, there is a comment that reads "Might have something to do with a certain kind of rotatable structure." "...G—Give me back that piece of paper, or I'll take it!"

149979.name: Edited Note
149979.desc: Pela's notes with her elegant handwriting. The clues you find in the Fragmentum are recorded here. In the note, there is a curved arrow pointing clockwise, another pointing counterclockwise, and another pointing clockwise. Next to the drawing, there is a comment that reads "Might have something to do with a certain kind of rotatable structure." "...G—Give me back that piece of paper, or I'll take it!"

149980.name: Training Certificate
149980.desc: A certificate for participants in restricted zone training. Evidence of having defeated the Silvermane Guards before.

149981.name: Training Certificate
149981.desc: A certificate for participants in restricted zone training. Evidence of having defeated the Silvermane Guards before.

149982.name: Training Certificate
149982.desc: A certificate for participants in restricted zone training. Evidence of having defeated the Silvermane Guards before.

149991.name: Box of Metal Plates and Bandages
149991.desc: Medical supplies urgently needed by Natasha. "A full box of metal plates and bandages, exactly what Natasha needs."

150000.name: Hanu's Adventure Foreword
150000.desc: A limited edition cartoon storybook released by Clock Studios, narrating a tale where Hanu shrinks in size and saves Dreamville... The book includes occasional peculiar dialogue interspersed throughout.

150001.name: Hanu's Adventure Part 1, Chapter 1
150001.desc: A limited edition cartoon storybook released by Clock Studios, narrating a tale where Hanu shrinks in size and saves Dreamville... The book includes occasional peculiar dialogue interspersed throughout.

150002.name: Hanu's Adventure Part 1, Chapter 2
150002.desc: A limited edition cartoon storybook released by Clock Studios, narrating a tale where Hanu shrinks in size and saves Dreamville... The book includes occasional peculiar dialogue interspersed throughout.

150003.name: Hanu's Adventure Part 1, Chapter 3
150003.desc: A limited edition cartoon storybook released by Clock Studios, narrating a tale where Hanu shrinks in size and saves Dreamville... The book includes occasional peculiar dialogue interspersed throughout.

150004.name: Hanu's Adventure Part 1, Chapter 4
150004.desc: A limited edition cartoon storybook released by Clock Studios, narrating a tale where Hanu shrinks in size and saves Dreamville... The book includes occasional peculiar dialogue interspersed throughout.

150010.name: Recipe: Dream Syrup
150010.desc: A unique creation from Penacony, this syrup serves as a non-addictive tranquilizer, offering an ineffable experience of serenity and delight for a certain duration. "Its manufacturer claims this syrup has all the benefits of religion and alcohol without any of their drawbacks."

150011.name: Recipe: Classic SoulGlad
150011.desc: When it comes to SoulGlad, classic means the best. Despite three attempts to modify the formula, the SoulGlad company was compelled to return to the original recipe due to complaints from dissatisfied customers each time. "Our double-blind tests show that over 70% of customers failed to discern the difference between the new formula and the original one."

150012.name: Recipe: Bright Future
150012.desc: "One day, we will have a real house." With a cup of coffee in her hand, your wife says. "It will have a yard where we can grow flowers, a hall where we can dance, a transparent attic where we can gaze at the stars — and ideally, a small dog to cuddle and fall asleep with. That would truly be the truly blissful life." You smile in silence and propose a toast. The warm vapor swirls and ascends, gently caressing the ceiling before dissipating. "A bright future exists only in dreams."

150013.name: Recipe: Daring Wager
150013.desc: The poker game continued, reaching the fourth round. The man could not stop himself from checking his hand — his confidence had long since wavered. "A true gambler won't hesitate to call, even if the chances of winning are impossibly small..." The young man on the opposite side of the table snickered, pushing all his chips forward. "All in." "Being content is a virtue for mortals, whereas hesitation is a fatal flaw for gamblers."

150014.name: Recipe: Pika White Grape Soda
150014.desc: This soda made of fermented white grapes tastes both sour and bitter. It serves as an exceptionally revitalizing remedy for summer heat, and consuming it often results in sneezing and a runny nose. According to those who have tasted it, it feels like a cold hand pressed against your neck. "Pika... Ah-choo...!"

150015.name: Recipe: Eternal Endurance
150015.desc: "Insufficient active ingredient. Experiment failed." The scholar, frustrated by his 106,001st failure, randomly poked at the terminal. Developing a new poison formula proved to be much more challenging than anticipated. If he couldn't produce results by tomorrow... His mind was overwhelmed with worry, leading him to knock over the test tube rack on the table. The liquids from two unidentified containers mixed, releasing a pungent odor... "The 106,002nd attempt. Result: Successful."

150016.name: Special Drink "El Dorado"
150016.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'El Dorado' in your honor, Dreamchaser —" "To golden dreams."

150017.name: Special Drink "The Premature Burial"
150017.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'The Premature Burial' in your honor, dreamer —" "To bringing time to a standstill."

150018.name: Special Drink "Dream Within Dream"
150018.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'Dream Within Dream' in your honor, sober one —" "To our forebearers who dug their own graves."

150019.name: Special Drink "The Big Sleep"
150019.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'The Big Sleep' in your honor, lost sheep —" "Here's to the ghosts of the past."

150020.name: Special Drink "The Long Goodbye"
150020.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'The Long Goodbye' in your honor, watcher —" "To a bitter childhood."

150021.name: Special Drink "Farewell, My Lovely"
150021.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'Farewell, My Lovely' in your honor, seeker of truth —" "To unfinished business."

150022.name: Special Drink "A Ticket to the Boneyard"
150022.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'A Ticket to the Boneyard' in your honor, Nameless —" "To the dead and the dying."

150023.name: Special Drink "Even the Wicked"
150023.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'Even the Wicked' in your honor, Trailblazer —" "To the sad truth."

150024.name: Special Drink "Time to Murder and Create"
150024.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'Time to Murder and Create' in your honor, innovator —" "To great vengeance."

150025.name: Special Drink "El Dorado"
150025.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'El Dorado' in your honor, Dreamchaser —" "To golden dreams."

150026.name: Special Drink "The Premature Burial"
150026.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'The Premature Burial' in your honor, dreamer —" "To bringing time to a standstill."

150027.name: Special Drink "Dream Within Dream"
150027.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'Dream Within Dream' in your honor, sober one —" "To our forebearers who dug their own graves."

150028.name: Special Drink "The Big Sleep"
150028.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'The Big Sleep' in your honor, lost sheep —" "Here's to the ghosts of the past."

150029.name: Special Drink "The Long Goodbye"
150029.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'The Long Goodbye' in your honor, watcher —" "To a bitter childhood."

150030.name: Special Drink "Farewell, My Lovely"
150030.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'Farewell, My Lovely' in your honor, seeker of truth —" "To unfinished business."

150031.name: Special Drink "A Ticket to the Boneyard"
150031.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'A Ticket to the Boneyard' in your honor, Nameless —" "To the dead and the dying."

150032.name: Special Drink "Even the Wicked"
150032.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'Even the Wicked' in your honor, Trailblazer —" "To the sad truth."

150033.name: Special Drink "Time to Murder and Create"
150033.desc: A special concoction tailored exclusively for you by the drinksmith Gallagher. "Raise this glass of 'Time to Murder and Create' in your honor, innovator —" "To great vengeance."

150034.name: Cork Coaster
150034.desc: An item Siobhan gifted you. It's said to have a mysterious property that allows entry to monsters' Emoscape. A commonplace cork coaster adorned with the emblematic logo of the Dreamjolt Hostelry. "...The purpose of a coaster is to soften the impact of collisions."

150035.name: Nightingale Statue Clue
150035.desc: It seems that all it takes for this door to open is returning the statue to its original position...

150036.name: Big Ticker's Broken Heart (I)
150036.desc: A single part of a lost heart that has fallen into an existential crisis. "They said that the Dreamscape Ticker isn't the same as Clockie at all, just a scrapped early Clockie prototype..."

150037.name: Big Ticker's Broken Heart (II)
150037.desc: A single part of a lost heart that has fallen into an existential crisis. "Please... just leave me be, Clockie. I just don't know how to face you... because I'm just a failed product."

150038.name: Big Ticker's Broken Heart (III)
150038.desc: A single part of a lost heart that has fallen into an existential crisis. "I... I'll never be qualified to be the real you. Just give up, Clockie!"

150039.name: Dreamjolt Hostelry Group Photo
150039.desc: A group photo of all the members of Dreamjolt Hostelry given to you by Starlet. "There is no doubt that you are an excellent drinksmith. Thank you for your efforts."

150040.name: Dreamy Cone (Three Flavors)
150040.desc: What does the taste of a sweet dream resemble? This question lacks a definitive answer. Hence, Dreamy Cones were introduced with an initial offering of over twenty distinct flavors. However, as time passed, only three prominent flavors endured, each representing a popular scenario found in dreams. "So, the three most popular scenarios are... memory loss, car crash, and terminal illness?"

150041.name: Floatdisc Burger
150041.desc: This burger earns its name from the crunchy disc-shaped flaky chip nestled between the buns, and only a few individuals can consume it in a dignified way. In certain taverns, devouring a Floatdisc Burger without using your hands has become somewhat of a legendary challenge. "Why is it that some Halovians always find fault with its appearance?"

150042.name: Clockie Pizza (Whole)
150042.desc: Resembling a clock, this pizza is precisely divided into twelve equal-sized slices, making it the perfect food for parties. "What is the meaning behind the unique shape of this food? Some believe it pays homage to a mysterious wealthy individual, while others see it as a reminder to cherish each passing moment."

150043.name: Potato Fries Sundae
150043.desc: Strictly, the Potato Fries Sundae is not merely a food but a unique culinary experience that can only be realized within a dream world. In this realm, potato fries never go soft because of cooling down, and the ice cream never melts because of warming up. Cold and heat achieve perfect harmony here. "Finally, no more upset stomachs."

150044.name: Oak Cake Rolls
150044.desc: Legend has it that poor inhabitants of border planets would add wood chips to their bread to satiate their hunger. Over time, this practice evolved into a peculiar tradition among aristocrats, symbolizing a "reverence" for the humble past. This product features a variety of botanical additives, closely resembling an oak branch in terms of both appearance and composition, and only the most ambitious and determined individuals can consume it. "Politicians from the Oak Family take pride in eating it without flinching, for they believe it to be a formidable feat."

150045.name: Pika White Grape Soda
150045.desc: This soda made of fermented white grapes tastes both sour and bitter. It serves as an exceptionally revitalizing remedy for summer heat, and consuming it often results in sneezing and a runny nose. According to those who have tasted it, it feels like a cold hand pressed against your neck. "Pika... Ah-choo...!"

150046.name: Classic SoulGlad
150046.desc: When it comes to SoulGlad, classic means the best. Despite three attempts to modify the formula, the SoulGlad company was compelled to return to the original recipe due to complaints from dissatisfied customers each time. "Our double-blind tests show that over 70% of customers failed to discern the difference between the new formula and the original one."

150047.name: Trailbirder ID Card
150047.desc: The personalized bird ID card just for you in the game Origami Bird Clash. It's said to be customized by the system based on your appearance.

150048.name: Huaiyan's Testimony
150048.desc: General of the Xianzhou Zhuming and Yunli's grandfather. Yunli had intended to talk to her grandfather about Guyun today, but the sword was stolen.

150049.name: Yunli's Testimony
150049.desc: The prime suspect of this incident. She swore to completely melt every one of the cursed swords forged by her father, including Guyun.

150050.name: Paavo's Testimony
150050.desc: A Kalevalan envoy in charge of diplomatic affairs. He led a delegation to return the ancient sword, Guyun, to the Xianzhou. Though Yunli calls it a cursed sword, Paavo firmly believes Guyun to be the sword of a hero as told in the legends from his home.

150051.name: Master Gongshu's Testimony
150051.desc: An artisan from the Artisanship Commission and the craftsman responsible for repairing Guyun. He checked on how Guyun was stored after you reminded him to keep the sword safe. Guyun was yet to be stolen at that time.

150052.name: Intact Lock
150052.desc: The lock on the sword casket that Guyun was stored in. Given its intact lock, the thief either had the key to the casket or it was never locked to begin with.

150053.name: Rose Petal
150053.desc: A rose petal that was caught in the hinge mechanism. You can only think of one person who would leave behind this ostentatious trace wherever he goes.

150055.name: "Wardance 21-Gun Salute"
150055.desc: The jade abacus given to you by artillery system engineer Old Bai of the Skysplitter. It contains a program he wrote that enables the Skysplitter to fire twenty-one ceremonial cannons. "You must fire the cannons. You absolutely must. You'll regret it if you don't!"

150056.name: "Abyss of Fate" Hymn Tablet
150056.desc: A tablet inscribed with hymns and other writings, prophesying towards the end. It is said that within these fragments lies a secret so profound that it longs to be uncovered. "Prophecies never carry their message in plain words." — Anonymous Priest

150057.name: "Strife Ruins" Hymn Tablet
150057.desc: A tablet inscribed with hymns and other writings, prophesying towards the end. It is said that within these fragments lies a secret so profound that it longs to be uncovered. "Prophecies never carry their message in plain words." — Anonymous Priest

150059.name: "Eternal Holy City" Hymn Tablet
150059.desc: A tablet inscribed with hymns and other writings, prophesying towards the end. It is said that within these fragments lies a secret so profound that it longs to be uncovered. "Prophecies never carry their message in plain words." — Anonymous Priest

150060.name: Coin of Whimsy
150060.desc: The token of the Trickery Titan. Like the Titan's mythical form, the coin has two faces, one smiling, one crying, effortlessly flipping in the air. It was originally used by fraudsters as counterfeit coins to replace the Balance Coins. Fearing that such actions would invoke Talanton's punishment, they crafted it in the image of Zagreus, seeking the blessing of Trickery. However, as time passed, these coins became more precious than the Balance Coins due to the difficulty of their creation, becoming a favorite collectible of nobles and artists — though this could also be one of Zagreus' tricks. "Rolling coins turn into wheels, thieves conceal their forms, gamblers wager fortunes." — Ode of Trickery

150061.name: A Bunch of Rainbows
150061.desc: A bunch of tiny Rainbow blossoms. In floriography, it means "the beauty of the ordinary."

150062.name: A Stalk of Marquise
150062.desc: A stalk of exquisite Marquise blossoms. It represents a status of prestige.

150079.desc: A tome containing prophecies. Upon closer inspection, one will discover that the scroll is woven from golden threads. "There is a prophecy within that will only be revealed to the one who opens the scroll."

150080.name: Conch Echo: Kindling
150080.desc: Feed this memory into the Recording Conch and listen closely — the voice may speak of nature's secrets or confide hidden thoughts. This is a memory about the "Hearth." "Steaming tea, knitted scarves, and a tale without end."

150081.name: Conch Echo: Winter
150081.desc: Feed this memory into the Recording Conch and listen closely — the voice may speak of nature's secrets or confide hidden thoughts. This is a memory of "Snow." "You used up all the paint? What did you draw?" "I think... just pure white."

150082.name: Conch Echo: In the Rain
150082.desc: Feed this memory into the Recording Conch and listen closely — the voice may speak of nature's secrets or confide hidden thoughts. This is a memory of "A Rainy Night." "I stretched out my palm and pressed it against the glass." "It brought a coolness to my skin... and something that kept stirring inside me."

150083.name: Conch Echo: Rumble
150083.desc: Feed this memory into the Recording Conch and listen closely — the voice may speak of nature's secrets or confide hidden thoughts. This is a memory of "Thunder." "I like thunderstorms." "Huh? Weren't you scared of thunder? You always came running to my place..." "Yeah. That's why I like them."

150084.name: Portentous Goldwoven: "Lightless Chapel"
150084.desc: A tome containing prophecies. Upon closer inspection, one will discover that the scroll is woven from golden threads. "There is a prophecy within that will only be revealed to the one who opens the scroll."

150085.name: Portentous Goldwoven: "Lightless Chapel"
150085.desc: A tome containing prophecies. Upon closer inspection, one will discover that the scroll is woven from golden threads. "There is a prophecy within that will only be revealed to the one who opens the scroll."

150086.name: "Fruit of Time"
150086.desc: Obtained by solving the nymph prophecy puzzle for each Garmentmaker. Redeemable at An Eternal Page for unique keepsakes. It is the treasure at the end of the adventure, and the benchmark of a legend's prologue, born from the brand-new structure born after the Era Nova. Influenced by Amphorean sagas of heroes, it presents itself in the current space-time as a golden apple. "To give civilizations to time, to give years their life."

150087.name: Portentous Goldwoven: Aedes Elysiae
150087.desc: A scroll with prophecies inscribed. Upon closer inspection, one will discover that the scroll is woven from golden threads. "There is a prophecy within that will only be revealed to the one who opens the scroll."

150088.name: Heroic Variable
150088.desc: A minute "variable" of the world, born from the brand-new structure born after the Era Nova. Each time you gaze at it, memories surge like a tide — as if a fragment of Amphoreus's years lies sealed within. It might help you in a time you've not yet reached. "Is it the legend-writers who become heroes, or must one first become a hero to write legends?"

150089.name: Memchelin 4-Star Certificate
150089.desc: A 4-star certification from the Memchelin Gourmet Committee represents the highest recognition for a restaurant. To date, only one restaurant in the Membrance Maze has earned this prestigious honor. "Never forget, the purpose of cooking is to bring happiness to our diners."

150090.name: Memchelin Star Award
150090.desc: An award from the Memchelin Gourmet Committee is the ultimate proof of excellence that every restaurant dreams of. "Target: Memchelin 4-star!"
