250201.name: Malfunctioning Chip
250201.desc: Attacking a debuffed enemy deals Additional DMG to them.

250202.name: Defective Suppression Chip
250202.desc: When an enemy is defeated, all other enemies' actions are greatly delayed.

250203.name: Emergency Reboot Chip
250203.desc: When struck by a killing blow, instead of being knocked down, immediately restores HP and gains an additional turn. This effect can only trigger 1 time per battle.

250204.name: Trotter Patch Chip
250204.desc: When equipped by a Trotter, greatly Enhances it.

250205.name: Morale Activation Chip
250205.desc: After an ally launches an attack, receive Morale. Morale increases all ally stats.

250207.name: Performance Allocation Chip
250207.desc: When an enemy is defeated, regenerates 1 Energy for all other allies, 1 time per turn.

250208.name: Efficiency Optimization Chip
250208.desc: After entering combat, reduces the Energy required for Ultimate by 1. Energy can be reduced by up to 2 points max.

250209.name: High Load-Low Speed Chip
250209.desc: Greatly increases ATK and greatly reduces SPD.

250210.name: Sudden Evasion Chip
250210.desc: During the first 2 turns of battle, greatly reduces DMG received.

250211.name: Safe Mode Chip
250211.desc: Greatly reduces ATK and greatly increases Max HP.

250212.name: Threshold Disruption Chip
250212.desc: When attacking enemy targets with HP percentage greater than a certain amount, greatly increases the DMG dealt by the attack.

250213.name: Freeze Loophole Chip
250213.desc: Upon entering battle, causes all enemies to Freeze.

250214.name: Shield System Chip
250214.desc: Greatly increases chance to be attacked. Upon entering battle, obtains a Shield.

250215.name: Backstage Enhancement Chip
250215.desc: The wearer's ATK is greatly increased when it is not currently their turn.

250216.name: Sudden Interjection Chip
250216.desc: After the first action, immediately gains an additional turn.

250217.name: Wind Shear Loophole Chip
250217.desc: After attacking, there is a chance of inflicting Wind Shear on the target.

250218.name: Matrix Iteration Chip
250218.desc: After using their Ultimate, the wearer restores a massive amount of HP.

250219.name: Attack Interception Chip
250219.desc: At the end of the wearer's action, they gain a Barrier that nullifies all DMG received except DoTs.

250220.name: Auto-Repair Chip
250220.desc: Restores a minor amount of HP after the wearer takes action. Each time this is triggered, the HP restored increases.

250221.name: Data Retrieval Chip
250221.desc: After defeating an enemy, the wearer restores a massive amount of HP.

250222.name: Parallel Enhancement Chip
250222.desc: After using an attack, increase DMG received by the wearer and the attacked enemies.

250223.name: Saturated Activation Chip
250223.desc: When the wearer's first turn begins, immediately regenerates a certain amount of Energy.

250224.name: Quick Command Chip
250224.desc: Consume all Skill Points after using a Basic ATK or Skill to take an extra action. This cannot be triggered consecutively.

250225.name: Shieldbreaker Chip
250225.desc: When attacking Shielded enemy targets, greatly increases the DMG dealt by the attack.

250226.name: Functional Overdraft Chip
250226.desc: After attacking the enemy target, the wearer consumes their own HP and greatly Advances their action Forward.

250227.name: Energy Recycling Chip
250227.desc: After using their Ultimate to defeat enemy targets, the wearer regenerates their Energy to max.

250228.name: Computation Lock Chip
250228.desc: Greatly increases ATK, but disables Ultimate.

250229.name: Cleansing Chip
250229.desc: Dispels one buff on the target when attacking. If the buff is successfully dispelled, increase the DMG of this attack.

250230.name: Firewall Chip
250230.desc: Increases Max HP and greatly increases the chance of enemies attacking the wearer.

250231.name: Negative Load Algorithm Chip
250231.desc: Increases DMG dealt based on the number of debuffs on the wearer.

250232.name: Deep Clean Chip
250232.desc: At the end of the turn, removes all debuffs from the wearer, and removes 1 debuff from each of the other allies.

250320.name: Aether Spirit Upgrade Data
250320.desc: A data chip used to increase Aether Spirit levels in the Aetherium Wars.

250401.name: Corridor of Fading Echoes Mastery Mark
250401.desc: In the game Aetherium Wars, the proof of passing the Victory Zone test can be obtained by collecting four Mastery Marks, which qualifies you to participate in the championship. The Victory Zone of the Corridor of Fading Echoes grants you this proof, signifying your victory against the formidable championship contenders, Serval and Pela. "You are a calm, yet passionate player!"

250402.name: Cloudford Mastery Mark
250402.desc: In the game Aetherium Wars, the proof of passing the Victory Zone test can be obtained by collecting four Mastery Marks, which qualifies you to participate in the championship. The Victory Zone of Cloudford grants you this proof, signifying your victory against the formidable championship contender, Master Gongshu. "You are a skilled and masterful player!"

250403.name: Herta Space Station Mastery Mark
250403.desc: In the game Aetherium Wars, the proof of passing the Victory Zone test can be obtained by collecting four Mastery Marks, which qualifies you to participate in the championship. The Victory Zone of Herta Space Station grants you this proof, signifying your victory against the formidable championship contender, Herta. "You are an intelligent player!"

250404.name: Great Mine Mastery Mark
250404.desc: In the game Aetherium Wars, the proof of passing the Victory Zone test can be obtained by collecting four Mastery Marks, which qualifies you to participate in the championship. The Victory Zone of Great Mine grants you this proof, signifying your victory against the formidable championship contender, Giovanni. "You are a player who knows how to enjoy!"

250601.name: Road of the Mundanite
250601.desc: After displaying this in the Probability Museum, the starting Cosmic Fragments in the Divergent Universe increases by 20.

250602.name: Herta: Collector's Edition
250602.desc: After displaying this in the Probability Museum, the Divergent Universe Curio store in Store Domains will increase the amount of purchasable Curios by 1.

250603.name: Pursuit's End
250603.desc: After displaying this in the Probability Museum, the Heat usable for Blessing Enhancement increases by 1 point in the Divergent Universe First Plane's Workbench of Creation.

250604.name: Dr. Ratio — Bespoke Version
250604.desc: After displaying this in the Probability Museum, the amount of Cosmic Fragments needed to overwrite Equations in the Divergent Universe's Workbench of Creation decreases by 10.

250605.name: Hero's Trail
250605.desc: After this item is placed in the Probability Museum, your team will recover 2 Technique Points after entering a Boss Domain in Divergent Universe.

250606.name: Mem (Cuter Version)
250606.desc: After displaying this in the Probability Museum, receive 1 attempt to reset Blessings for free in the Divergent Universe Third Plane's Workbench of Creation.

250607.name: Avalon: Ever the Distant Utopia
250607.desc: After this item is placed in the Probability Museum, restores HP equal to 20% of Max HP for all allies when entering a domain in Divergent Universe.

250608.name: Command Spell Umbra
250608.desc: After displaying this in the Probability Museum, the Cosmic Fragments obtained after a battle victory in the Divergent Universe increases by 1.

250700.name: Tactical Codex: Feint Attack
250700.desc: When an ally uses their Ultimate, their action is immediately Advanced Forward, and Weakness Break Efficiency increases.

250701.name: Tactical Codex: Early Reveal
250701.desc: Allies gain Early Reveal. In the effect duration, after every attack, launch 1 attack against all enemies that have been hit and inflict them with the debuff.

250702.name: Tactical Codex: Lie in Wait
250702.desc: Applies Burn, Shock, Bleed, and Wind Shear on all enemies, and causes all enemies to immediately take action, triggering the DoT effects.

250703.name: Tactical Codex: Out of Thin Air
250703.desc: All allies immediately activate their Ultimates.

250704.name: Tactical Codex: Uproot the Cause
250704.desc: Causes allied character to immediately take another action after their next action and increases their DMG dealt.

250705.name: Tactical Codex: Stealing Their Thunder
250705.desc: All allies immediately take action, recover Skill Points, and increases Weakness Break Efficiency.

250706.name: Tactical Beverage: Pulse Energy
250706.desc: For every target on the field, increases DMG by allies.

250707.name: Tactical Beverage: Blu Bull
250707.desc: After using Ultimate to deal DMG, increases Ultimate DMG dealt to the target of the attack.

250708.name: Tactical Beverage: Devil's Hand
250708.desc: For each DoT status the enemy target is afflicted with, increases the DMG taken by them.

250709.name: Tactical Beverage: Westroc Super Drink
250709.desc: For each target an ally defeats, regenerates a small amount of Energy.

250710.name: Tactical Beverage: Mighty Quench
250710.desc: After triggering Follow-Up ATK, increases DMG received by target.

250711.name: Tactical Beverage: High Energy SoulGlad
250711.desc: Increases Break Effect. There is a chance of recovering Skill Points when dealing Break DMG.

251001.name: Tuskpir
251001.desc: Tuskpirs originate in the Xianzhou Zhuming. It is a wondrous creature that feeds upon human dreams and is often used to treat psychological ailments involving anxiety and unease.
come_from: Pet obtained after the Luminary Wardance event

251002.name: Bubbles
251002.desc: How do you raise a little chimera? Add a bit of liveliness, a dash of competitive spirit, and a love for water... Uh-oh, too much of everything!
come_from: A pet obtained from the Seal Slammers event

251003.name: Complainer
251003.desc: A registered little chimera at the Garden of Life who prefers sharing opinions about everything around them rather than focusing on actual work.

252000.name: Solemn Scarlet! Conductor Outfit
252000.desc: An outfit for the conductor. They can change into it using Pom-Pom's Coatroom in the Party Car.

252001.name: Clamoring Fry-Master! Chef Outfit Set
252001.desc: An outfit for the conductor. They can change into it using Pom-Pom's Coatroom in the Party Car.
come_from: Obtained from the "Cosmic Home Décor Guide" event

252002.name: Sweet Dreams! Pajamas Set
252002.desc: An outfit for the conductor. They can change into it using Pom-Pom's Coatroom in the Party Car.
come_from: Available at the Gift of Stardust store

252106.name: Reroll Coin
252106.desc: A special item used in Guest Occurrences. Can be used to reroll the random wheel once.

252125.name: Diamond
252125.desc:
Used to request Assistants and collect Memory Cards.
Can be obtained by completing Exhibition missions, Exhibition Occurrences, Exhibition achievements, leveling up Assistants, and more.

252126.name: Inspiration Points
252126.desc:
Used to unlock research content.
Can be obtained by increasing venue levels, completing exhibition missions, etc.

252127.name: Gold Coin
252127.desc:
The most basic resource for unlocking booths and increasing assistant levels.
Accumulate enough Gold Coins to increase Venue Level.

Gold Coin units from smallest to largest: K (thousand), M (million), B (billion), T (trillion), followed by AA, BB, CC... and so on.
Each adjacent unit is 1000 times larger than the previous.

252128.name: Standard Admission Ticket
252128.desc:
Used for Standard Invitations.
Can be obtained by completing missions, Exhibition Occurrences, increasing the Venue Level, and more.

252129.name: Golden Admission Ticket
252129.desc:
Used for Golden Invitations.
Can be obtained through missions, Exhibition Occurrences, increasing the Venue Level, and more.

252130.name: Resplendent Admission Ticket
252130.desc:
Used for Resplendent Invitation.
Can be obtained through missions, Exhibition Occurrences, increasing the Venue Level, and more.

252131.name: Memory Card Voucher
252131.desc:
Used to pull Memory Cards.
Can be obtained by increasing venue levels and completing exhibition events and missions.

253000.name: Journey Reblazed
253000.desc: As you traverse a distant path and look back on the silver rails, the origin of the journey continues to shine radiantly. Look, that was your first decision.

253001.name: Travel Invitation
253001.desc: Every single star has its own story amidst the boundless starry seas. The Trailblaze never ends — venture into the unknown and explore even more wondrous worlds!

253002.name: Skypillar
253002.desc: The giant bears the weight of heaven in silence, earning worship and reverence from all. Without it, everything would inevitably crumble.

254000.name: {NICKNAME}'s Free Will
254000.desc: Every footprint left in the sea of stars is a proof of the heart's desire.

254001.name: {NICKNAME}'s Moments of Joy
254001.desc: In the endless river of time, each drop of joy is worthy of a place in the pockets of memory, to be treasured eternally and savored time and time again.

Obtainable through Aurum Alley Streetside Events

come_from: Obtained by completing investigation requests from the Ghostly Grove

270003.name: Commemorative Badge
270003.desc: A commemorative badge from the band's performance, proving your contribution to the success of the music party. It can be used to claim rewards from performance remunerations.

270004.name: Melody of Celebration
270004.desc: A melody often played at Phagousa's banquets, now resounding once more with your victory. Can be used at the Prize Exchange to increase the Carnival Level and claim rewards.

270005.name: Seal Token
270005.desc: Handcrafted "Seal Tokens" by Apophis, each bearing a unique mark. Can be used to purchase baby seals at the Baby Seal Shop.

281001.name: Merchant Guild's Funds
come_from: Obtained from Inventory Arrangement at the Aurum Alley Dock

281005.name: Tips
281005.desc: The tips given by the monsters who patronize the Dreamjolt Hostelry. Can be used to redeem rewards in the Revenue Statistics.

281013.name: Neural Impulse
281013.desc: An indescribable material. Used to unlock abilities in the Simulated Universe: Gold and Gears.

281014.name: Ordinary Dice
281014.desc: A basic item for moving forward on the Cosmodyssey map.

281015.name: Trailblaze Funds
281015.desc: A mysterious game token materialized from the trailblazing experience. Contribute to Pom-Pom to convert them to Trailblaze blessings.

281016.name: Remote Dice
281016.desc: Item used for moving forward on the Cosmodyssey map. You can select which Dice Face you want.

281017.name: Reroll Coin
281017.desc: A special item used to backtrack in Board Encounters. It allows you to re-roll the die again.

281018.name: Inspiration
281018.desc: Indescribable materials used to unlock abilities in the Divergent Universe.

281019.name: Raccoon Tokens
281019.desc: The hard-earned personal savings of the Galactic Baseballer. Can be used to purchase baseballs in the Cosmic Store.

281020.name: Branch of Rites
281020.desc: Indescribable materials used to unlock the ability system in Protean Hero.

281022.name: Synchronicity Points
281022.desc: Important research results. Used to increase the Synchronicity Level in the Divergent Universe.

281025.name: Wardance Sword Badge
281025.desc: Commemorative badge awarded to the winner of the Wardance. Can be used to redeem Wardance Plaudits.

281026.name: Conjecture
281026.desc: A value you can accumulate or spend to strengthen Support systems in the Simulated Universe: Unknowable Domain.

281027.name: Raccoon Gold Coin
281027.desc: A currency common across the cosmos. Can be used to purchase items in the Cosmic Store.

281028.name: Cosmic Reputation
281028.desc: Reputation gained by the Galactic Baseballer in their adventure. This can be used to claim rewards provided by the Planetary Safety Committee.

281031.name: Gold Coin
281031.desc: The core economic resource in Currency Wars gameplay, used for purchasing squad members, increasing Experience, and refreshing the Store.

281032.name: Equivalent Banknote
281032.desc: Obtained through Currency Wars gameplay, can be used to activate "Advantage Layout."

281033.name: Ascension Points
281033.desc: Obtained through Currency Wars gameplay, can be used to increase your "Ascension Level."

281034.name: Experience
281034.desc: Experience material used to increase the team's size in Currency Wars. Automatically gains 2 points after clearing each Node. Can also be purchased with Gold Coins

281035.name: Free Refresh
281035.desc: A resource used to refresh the Store in Currency Wars. When this resource is available, refreshing the Store will not consume Gold Coins.

281037.name: Chrysos Invitation Ticket
281037.desc: A special invitation ticket for the "Chimera World Tournament" that unlocks chimera trainers you want to fight alongside with in the selection interface. It can be earned by participating in the tournament.

281038.name: Bounce-Bounce Snack
281038.desc: A special snack beloved by all creations. Can be used to cheer for creations in the "Snack Dash" event and exchange for rewards.

300002.name: Gift of the Pathstriders
300002.desc: Gifts between Pathstriders. Select one material of your choice.

300003.name: Grand Gift of the Pathstriders
300003.desc: Gifts between Pathstriders. Select one rare material of your choice.

300011.name: Treasure of the Starry Seas
300011.desc: A treasure left by the Nameless. Select one Light Cone of your choice.

300012.name: Treasure of the Starry Seas
300012.desc: A treasure left by the Nameless. Select one Light Cone of your choice.

300013.name: Jewels of the Starry Seas
300013.desc: A precious treasure drifting in the endless sea of stars. Select one Light Cone of your choice.

300019.name: Memo-Keeping Light Casket
300019.desc:
The container used by the Garden of Recollection to store Light Cones. You can choose to obtain one of the following 4-star Light Cones after opening it:
Quid Pro Quo, Fermata, We Are Wildfire, River Flows in Spring, Past and Future, Woof! Walk Time!, The Seriousness of Breakfast, Victory In a Blink

300020.desc:

300021.name: Sparkle's Wondrous Pack
300021.desc: A carefully prepared present from a certain Masked Fool.

300031.name: Gift of the Stars
300031.desc: A fine-looking envelope containing a custom-made ticket.

300041.name: Supplies Material Box (Standard)
300041.desc:
The assistance provided by Herta to the Astral Express. Upon use, you can select one item to obtain from the following materials:
· Lifeless Blade
· Arrow of the Demon Slayer
· Key of Knowledge
· Oath of Steel
· Obsidian of Desolation
· Ancestral Hymn
· Sprout of Life

300042.name: Supplies Material Box (Specialized)
300042.desc:
The assistance provided by Herta to the Astral Express. Upon use, you can select one item to obtain from the following materials:
· Worldbreaker Blade
· Arrow of the Starchaser
· Key of Wisdom
· Safeguard of Amber
· Obsidian of Obsession
· Stellaris Symphony
· Flower of Eternity

300051.name: Unclaimed Parcel
300051.desc: Unclaimed parcel. Opening them may yield random materials.

300052.name: Unclaimed Valuable Parcel
300052.desc: Unclaimed valuable parcel. Opening them may yield random rare materials.

300054.name: Big High Moral Bundle
300054.desc: You have so much morals to the point that the High Morals condensed into a greater physical existence and arrived at your side. "{NICKNAME}, you are a paragon!"

300055.name: Planetary Specialty Box
300055.desc: The Cosmos is full of peculiarities. This box contains specialties from various planets. Open it. You might find something you need inside.

300101.name: Express Supply Pass
300101.desc: Provisions prepared by the Express for Trailblazers. Claim with pass. "Dear conductor, can we not punch holes in the cards? I want to collect a whole collection of them."

300102.name: Nameless Glory (Unopened)
300102.desc: An unopened treasure. Use to gain the effect equivalent to purchasing Nameless Glory once.

300103.name: Nameless Medal (Unopened)
300103.desc: An unopened treasure. Use to gain the effect equivalent to purchasing Nameless Medal once.

300104.name: Honor Badge (Unopened)
300104.desc: An unopened treasure. Use it to upgrade the Nameless Glory to the Nameless Medal.

300200.name: The Adventurous Moles: Hidden Treasure
300200.desc: The on-sale collectors' edition containing the entirety of The Adventurous Moles: Hidden Treasure.

300202.name: Credbits
300202.desc: This currency, used by the Interastral Peace Corporation to settle accounts with its customers, is now widely accepted as the hard currency for space travel... Right?

300210.name: Portentous Goldwoven: Abyss of Fate
300210.desc: A tome containing prophecies. Upon closer inspection, one will discover that the scroll is woven from golden threads. "There is a prophecy within that will only be revealed to the one who opens the scroll."
